<html>
<head>
  <title>Mr. Roboto</title>

  <link
      href='http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Raleway:400,700'
      rel='stylesheet'
      type='text/css'/>

  <style>
    body {
      font-family: 'Raleway', sans-serif;
      background: url('static/roboto.png') no-repeat 60% 0%;
      font-size: 18px;
    }
    a {
      text-decoration: none;
    }
    a:link {
      color: white;
    }
    a:visited {
      color: white;
    }
    .alert {
      color: brown;
    }
    .plone {
      background-color: rgb(0,149,211);
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body class="plone">
  <h1>Welcome to mr.roboto!</h1>
  <p>It's the Plone webservice hub to interact with GitHub and Jenkins CI.</p>

  <p>With it you can do  the following:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <a href="${info.roboto_url}/log?token=XXX">Check the changelog</a>
      <em class="alert">Token needed</em>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="${info.roboto_url}/sources.json">See current sources</a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="${info.roboto_url}/checkouts.json">See current checkouts</a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="${info.roboto_url}/update-sources-and-checkouts?token=XXX">Update sources and checkouts</a>
      <em class="alert">Token needed</em>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="${info.roboto_url}/run/githubcommithooks?token=XXXXX">Re-create GitHub commit hooks</a>
      <em class="alert">Token needed</em>
    </li>
  </ul>

</body>
</html>
